OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F307A1775571066
OL,3,CMissed appointments and lost
OL,4,Clivelihoods in Scotland's ferry crisis
OL,6,FThe ferry service is also
OL,7,Finterconnected with social care
OL,8,Fprovisions on the island.
OL,10,FJohn Crawford's mother, Barbara,
OL,11,Fwanted to spend her final days on
OL,12,FArran. Diagnosed with dementia, John
OL,13,Fand his family cared for her in their
OL,14,Ffamily home in the south of the island.
OL,16,FKnown locally as the "Granite Lady"
OL,17,Fbecause of her Aberdonian roots, she
OL,18,Fbuilt a life on the island - a place
OL,19,Fher family had returned to for
OL,20,Fgenerations.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G10/19
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,308,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30711
SC,0011
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F307A1775571066
OL,3,CMissed appointments and lost
OL,4,Clivelihoods in Scotland's ferry crisis
OL,6,F"She had been coming to the island
OL,7,Fsince she was a small child", John
OL,8,Fsaid.
OL,10,F"Back in the days when there was no
OL,11,Felectricity in the cottages. The
OL,12,Fferries didn't stop at the harbour,
OL,13,Fyou jumped into a little boat and got
OL,14,Frowed ashore. She loved the place. And
OL,15,Fbecause she didn't have short-term
OL,16,Fmemory, her long-term memories meant
OL,17,Fthis felt like home. ultimately her
OL,18,Flife began and ended here in her mind.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G11/19
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,308,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30712
SC,0012
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F307A1775571066
OL,3,CMissed appointments and lost
OL,4,Clivelihoods in Scotland's ferry crisis
OL,6,F"The dementia was a fairly slow
OL,7,Fdecline," he said. "Her personality
OL,8,Fstayed the same. She was still Mum."
OL,10,FAs her condition worsened, Barbara's
OL,11,Fcare needs became more than her family
OL,12,Fwere able to provide.
OL,14,FShe had previously received respite
OL,15,Fcare in Montrose House, a care home on
OL,16,Fthe island and wanted to receive long-
OL,17,Fterm care at the home.
OL,19,FBudget cuts and staffing shortages saw
OL,20,Fthe number of beds in the home reduced
OL,21,Ffrom 30 to just 10.
OL,26,@oD@IO]oD@TOU
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G12/19
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,308,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30713
SC,0013
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F307A1775571066
OL,3,CMissed appointments and lost
OL,4,Clivelihoods in Scotland's ferry crisis
OL,6,FJohn was forced to find a care home on
OL,7,Fthe mainland, next to the ferry
OL,8,Fterminal, so he could be near his mum,
OL,9,Fand her friends on the island could
OL,10,Feasily visit Barbara.
OL,12,F"That's when she started to die," John
OL,13,Fsaid. "What was most important to her
OL,14,Fwas her home on Arran, living here and
OL,15,Fme. And when she left the island, she
OL,16,Flost both of those things."
OL,18,FJust two weeks after moving off the
OL,19,Fisland, Barbara died with her son at
OL,20,Fher side.
OL,26,@uD@GOU
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G13/19
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,308,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30714
SC,0014
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F307A1775571066
OL,3,CMissed appointments and lost
OL,4,Clivelihoods in Scotland's ferry crisis
OL,6,F"She was aware, and very sad she had
OL,7,Fto leave. She panicked she'd die off
OL,8,Fisland. She wanted to die on the
OL,9,Fisland."
OL,11,FFor John, the pain is compounded by
OL,12,Fthe belief that it didn't have to
OL,13,Fhappen.
OL,15,F"I guess the difficult thing was we
OL,16,Fhad a functioning, not just a
OL,17,Ffunctioning, actually a beautiful care
OL,18,Fhome on the island, and it's sitting
OL,19,Fthere with empty beds," he said.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G14/19
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,308,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30715
SC,0015
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F307A1775571066
OL,3,CMissed appointments and lost
OL,4,Clivelihoods in Scotland's ferry crisis
OL,6,F"People on an island this size should
OL,7,Fbe able to grow old and die here if
OL,8,Fthey want."
OL,10,FSubscribe free to our weekly
OL,11,Fnewsletter for exclusive and original
OL,12,Fcoverage from ITV News. Direct to your
OL,13,Finbox every Friday morning.
OL,15,FArran's economy is also under strain.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G15/19
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,308,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30716
SC,0016
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F307A1775571066
OL,3,CMissed appointments and lost
OL,4,Clivelihoods in Scotland's ferry crisis
OL,6,FTourism is a key industry, but the
OL,7,Funreliable ferry services affect
OL,8,Fincoming visitors. The constant
OL,9,Fnegative headlines and news of
OL,10,Fcancelled sailings mean many short-
OL,11,Fterm let providers and hotels have
OL,12,Fseen a marked decrease in the number
OL,13,Fof bookings.
OL,15,FThe island has become one of the UK's
OL,16,Fmost desirable locations for holiday
OL,17,Fhomes, driving up house prices and
OL,18,Fmaking it harder for workers to live
OL,19,Flocally.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G16/19
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,308,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30717
SC,0017
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F307A1775571066
OL,3,CMissed appointments and lost
OL,4,Clivelihoods in Scotland's ferry crisis
OL,6,FWithout reliable transport, staffing
OL,7,Fessential services becomes even more
OL,8,Fdifficult.
OL,10,FFor local businesses, the impact is
OL,11,Fimmediate.
OL,13,FFirst-time business owner Alastair
OL,14,FEccles-Wood, who runs The Bay Kitchen
OL,15,Fand Stores with his wife, says
OL,16,Fdeliveries are often delayed - or fail
OL,17,Fto arrive entirely.
OL,19,F"Sometimes our produce is just sitting
OL,20,Fin harbour on the mainland," he said.
OL,26,@|D@\O]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G17/19
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,308,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30718
SC,0018
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F307A1775571066
OL,3,CMissed appointments and lost
OL,4,Clivelihoods in Scotland's ferry crisis
OL,6,FShort-notice cancellations make it
OL,7,Falmost impossible to plan.
OL,9,F"You find out half an hour before the
OL,10,Fferry is due to sail that it's not
OL,11,Fgoing," he said. "With perishable
OL,12,Fgoods, that's just a loss."
OL,14,FHe wants the next Scottish government
OL,15,Fto prioritise small businesses like
OL,16,Fhis, which are already struggling with
OL,17,Fthe rising cost of energy bills and
OL,18,Frunning costs.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G18/19
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,308,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30719
SC,0019
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F307A1775571066
OL,3,CMissed appointments and lost
OL,4,Clivelihoods in Scotland's ferry crisis
OL,6,FWith voters preparing to go to the
OL,7,Fpolls on May 7th, people on Arran are
OL,8,Fasking whether any party can deliver a
OL,9,Flasting solution to the ferries crisis.
OL,11,FNew vessels are on the horizon, but
OL,12,Ffor communities like Arran, ferries
OL,13,Fare more than a mode of transport.
OL,15,FThey are a lifeline - and when they
OL,16,Ffail, everything else is put at risk.
OL,18,FFrom Westminster to Washington DC -
OL,19,Four political experts are across all
OL,20,Fthe latest key talking points. Listen
OL,21,Fto the latest episode below...
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G19/19
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
